'''''Pursuit''''' is a single-player [[arcade video game]] by [[Kee Games]], originally released in 1975. The player plays a [[World War I]] flying ace who tries to shoot down enemy planes. Gameplay is from a [[first person (video games)|first person]] perspective. ''Pursuit'' marks the first time [[Atari Inc.]] publicly acknowledged its relationship with Kee.<ref name="armchairarcade">
